import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from matplotlib.font_manager import FontProperties #   ,    .
import numpy as np
from matplotlib.ticker import AutoMinorLocator
In[]:
x = np.arange(0, 2*np.pi + 0.08, 0.08)
y = np.sin(x)
where_set = ['pre', 'post', 'mid']  #   ,    

#  
fig, axs = plt.subplots(3, 1, figsize=(16, 12))

font = FontProperties(family='serif',
                      style='normal',
                      weight='bold',
                      size=18)

# 
fig.suptitle(r'  $y(x) = \sin(x)$',
          fontproperties=font,
          alpha=0.85,
          color='#2c3e50',
          linespacing=1.4)

#  
for i, ax in enumerate(axs):
    ax.step(x, y, 'g-', marker = '.', markersize=4, linewidth=1,
            markeredgecolor=(0, 0, 139/255), markeredgewidth=1,
            markerfacecolor='dodgerblue', where=where_set[i],
            label=r'$y(x) = \sin(x)$')  # where -  ,    
    ax.grid()

    #    
    ax.legend(loc='upper left',
              fontsize=12,
              shadow=True,
              framealpha=0.9,
              facecolor='lightyellow',
              edgecolor='black',
              title='')

#   
axs[0].set_xlabel(r'$x$', fontsize=16, fontweight='medium', color='#34495e')
axs[0].set_ylabel(r'$y(x)$', fontsize=16, fontweight='medium', color='#34495e')

#  
for ax in axs:
    ax.grid(True)
    ax.xaxis.set_minor_locator(AutoMinorLocator())
    ax.yaxis.set_minor_locator(AutoMinorLocator())
    ax.tick_params(which='major', length=5, width=2)
    ax.tick_params(which='minor', length=2, width=1)
    ax.grid(which='major', linewidth=0.15, color='black')
    ax.grid(which='minor', linestyle='-', color='black', linewidth=0.15)

#  
plt.show()

x = np.arange(0, 2*np.pi + 0.2, 0.2)
y = 60 * np.cos(2*x) * np.cos(2*x)

#  
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))

font = FontProperties(family='serif',
                      style='normal',
                      weight='bold',
                      size=18)

# 
plt.title(r'  $y(x) = 60\cos^2(2x)$',
          fontproperties=font,
          alpha=0.85,
          color='#2c3e50',
          linespacing=1.4)

plt.stem(x, y,
         linefmt='r--',    #     
         markerfmt='^',    #  
         bottom=-5,
         label=r'$y(x) = 60\cos^2(2x)$');        # y-   (  0)

#   
plt.xlabel(r'$x$', fontsize=16, fontweight='medium', color='#34495e')
plt.ylabel(r'$y(x)$', fontsize=16, fontweight='medium', color='#34495e')

# 
plt.legend(loc='upper left',
           fontsize=12,
           shadow=True,
           framealpha=0.9,
           facecolor='lightyellow',
           edgecolor='black',
           title='')

#  
ax = plt.gca()
ax.grid(True)
ax.xaxis.set_minor_locator(AutoMinorLocator())
ax.yaxis.set_minor_locator(AutoMinorLocator())
ax.tick_params(which='major', length=5, width=2)
ax.tick_params(which='minor', length=2, width=1)
ax.grid(which='major', linewidth=0.15, color='black')
ax.grid(which='minor', linestyle='-', color='black', linewidth=0.15)

import pandas as pd

prices = np.array([13.0, 16.5, 17.0, 15.0, 14.2, 10.5, 23.0, 12.0, 22.5, 26.0, 18.5, 13.2, 25.8, 17.0, 18.0, 21.0, 15.5, 38.0, 30.0, 24.0]) # prices ($)

#  DataFrame
data = pd.DataFrame({
    '': x,
    ' ': y,
    '': prices
})

#   
table = data.groupby(' ').agg(
    _=('', 'size'),
    _=('', 'mean'),
    _=('', 'mean')
).reset_index()

#  
print(table)

#    
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 4))
ax.axis('tight')
ax.axis('off')
ax.table(cellText=table.values, colLabels=table.columns, loc='center', cellLoc='center', colColours=["#f2f2f2"]*table.shape[1])

plt.show()
